<p>You can use the <keyword conref="wskc_conref-l0wskc04.dita#conref-l0wskc04/vbnmpkg"/> verb to
generate internal and external PKA tokens. You can also generate RSA keys on another system and then
import them to the cryptographic coprocessor. To input a clear RSA key, create the token with the
<keyword conref="wskc_conref-l0wskc04.dita#conref-l0wskc04/vbnmpkb"/> verb and import it using the
<keyword conref="wskc_conref-l0wskc04.dita#conref-l0wskc04/vbnmpki"/> verb. To input an encrypted
RSA key, use the <keyword conref="wskc_conref-l0wskc04.dita#conref-l0wskc04/vbnmpki"/> verb.</p>
<p>In either case, use the <keyword conref="wskc_conref-l0wskc04.dita#conref-l0wskc04/vbnmpkb"/>
verb to create a skeleton key token as input (see <xref href="wskc_r_pkb.dita#l0wskc02_pkb"/>).</p>
<p>The <keyword conref="wskc_conref-l0wskc04.dita#conref-l0wskc04/vbnmpki"/> verb uses the clear
token from the <keyword conref="wskc_conref-l0wskc04.dita#conref-l0wskc04/vbnmpkb"/> verb or a clear
or encrypted token from the <keyword conref="wskc_conref-l0wskc04.dita#conref-l0wskc04/cca"/> system
to securely import the key token into operational form for the coprocessor to use. <keyword
conref="wskc_conref-l0wskc04.dita#conref-l0wskc04/cca"/> does not permit the export of the imported
PKA key.</p>
<p>The <keyword
conref="wskc_conref-l0wskc04.dita#conref-l0wskc04/vbnmpkx"></keyword> <ph>verb</ph> builds
a public key token from a private key token.</p>
<p>Application RSA public and private keys can be stored in the PKA
key storage file.</p>
